        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "There should be support fo LOCK IN SHARE MODE just as there if for FOR UPDATE. I'm willing to do the patch, but i didn't find enough information about standard SQL. PostgreSQL has FOR {UPDATE | SHARE} syntax for example (http:\/\/www.arpug.com.ar\/trac\/wiki\/sql-select.html#ClausulaFORUPDATEFORSHARE) . Adding this feature would suppose this locking methods to be exclusive with each other. A single method for selecting type seems more accurate.\r\n\r\nThank you for your attention."
        },
